^B@2^*Bcaitlin: ^*N|cp||at|If East has the DAQ, this hand will go down. One can give up and say, “Oh well, down one.”  However this hand exemplifies "exploration plays."  This means you do not touch the diamonds till you find out more about the East hand which is clearly defined as 15-17 balanced HCP. Once we see the @SAKQ, the @HJ,  and the @CA, we have 14 HCP.  Thus, East must have the @DQ but cannot have the @DA as that would add up to 18 HCP and we play 15-17 NT. Therefore, hold off on that diamond suit and explore first!  If West has the CA, then there is not much you can do as then East would have to have both the @DA and @DQ.|
